                        "description": "Our technicians run new copper refrigerant lines between outdoor and indoor units using proper brazing techniques (never compression fittings which can leak). Lines are insulated to prevent energy loss and condensation, properly sized for your system's capacity, pressure-tested for leaks before charging, and routed to minimize visual impact while maintaining efficiency. Electrical connections include appropriate wire gauge for system amperage, proper circuit breaker sizing and installation, disconnect switches for safety compliance, and thorough testing of all electrical components."
